modules.description: This module handles media type parsing, construction, and negotiation, primarily for HTTP content negotiation. It works with `Cohttp.Accept.media_range`, strings, and encoding types, supporting operations like matching accept headers, selecting preferred media types, and encoding/decoding values. Concrete use cases include negotiating response formats in REST APIs, constructing and deconstructing media types with parameters, and handling content encoding in HTTP requests and responses.

This module defines and manipulates CORS policies by specifying allowed headers and origins. It provides functions to add CORS headers to HTTP responses, check if a request's host matches allowed origins, and apply default CORS settings. It is used to control cross-origin resource sharing in HTTP services built with Cohttp, ensuring secure access from specified domains and with specified headers.

This module provides functions to parse, construct, and negotiate media types, particularly for HTTP content negotiation. It operates on `Cohttp.Accept.media_range`, strings, and encoding types, supporting operations such as matching accept headers, selecting preferred media types, and handling media type parameters. Use cases include determining response formats in REST APIs and managing content encoding in HTTP requests and responses.

This module handles cross-origin resource sharing and media type negotiation in HTTP services. It provides functions to manage CORS policies, including origin checks and header additions, and to parse and negotiate media types for content encoding and response formatting. It works with HTTP responses, media ranges, and request headers to enforce security policies and select appropriate data formats during API interactions.
